  <Subject Subject_ID="300134695">
    <Parent_Relationships>
      <Preferred_Parent>
        <Parent_Subject_ID>300137294</Parent_Subject_ID>
        <Relationship_Type>Parent/Child</Relationship_Type>
        <Historic_Flag>Current</Historic_Flag>
        <Parent_String>photographs by processing or presentation technique [300137294], photographs by technique [300127011], photographs [300046300], visual works by material or technique [300191091], visual works (works) [300191086], Visual Works (hierarchy name) [300179869], Visual and Verbal Communication (hierarchy name) [300264552], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Photographs in which the image is near life-size or larger. Distinct from the term "enlargements," which only indicates that a photograph has been produced from a smaller photograph. For photographs taken through a microscope use "photomicrographs."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Úsese para fotografías en que la imagen es de tamaño natural o mayor. Distinto del término "ampliación" que sólo indica que una fotografía ha sido producida a partir de una fotografía más pequeña. Para fotografías tomadas a través de un microscopio use "fotomicrografía".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Foto's waarbij het onderwerp vrijwel 1:1 of nog groter in beeld is gebracht, gemaakt met een macrolens of -ring. Te onderscheiden van de term 'vergrotingen', die aangeeft dat een foto van een kleiner negatief is gemaakt. Gebruik 'micro-opnamen' voor foto's die zijn gemaakt met behulp van een microscoop.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fotografie, bei der das Bild fast lebensgroß oder größer ist. Unterscheidet sich vom Begriff “Vergrößerung”, der nur darauf verweist, dass eine Fotografie von einem kleinen Foto hergestellt wurde. Für Fotografien, die durch ein Mikroskop aufgenommen werden, wird “Fotomikrographie” verwendet.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>意指影像尺寸與真實比例接近或更大的照片。「放大照片」(enlargements)則是指由小型照片所製作出來的照片影像。若是透過顯微鏡所拍攝的照片，請參見「顯微照片」(photomicrographs)。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
